Paris Saint-Germain are ready to offer an astonishing £61million to prise away Eden Hazard from Chelsea. 

The French champions, fined £49m for breaching Financial Fair Play guidelines only last month, have already paid Chelsea £50m for David Luiz.

They have also shown interest in Branislav Ivanovic, Oscar and Petr Cech but Hazard is the main prize and they believe Chelsea could sell.

