It is understood a Hazard representative met Sheik Tamim bin Hamad al-Thani, PSG’s owner in March. PSG can offer Hazard a five-year deal worth £230,000 a week.

Chelsea manager Jose Mourinho hopes to seal a £35m deal for Atletico Madrid’s Diego Costa before the World Cup starts on June 12 and is also keen on his teammates Tiago, Filipe Luis, Koke and Diego Godin. 

Talks to sign Barcelona midfielder Cesc Fabregas are ongoing while Chelsea scouts are closely monitoring Carlos Gruezo, the 19-year-old Stuttgart midfielder.

